      • searchCategories

        public SearchResponse<CategoryResponse> searchCategories(String keyword,
                                                Long categoryId,
                                                Boolean rootOnly,
                                                Enums.CategoryApiMap sortField,
                                                Boolean descending,
                                                Integer start,
                                                Integer limit,
                                                Boolean activeOnly)
                                                  throws SirqulException
        Search for categories.

        Target API Endpoint: /category/search
        Parameters:
        keyword - the keyword used to search
        categoryId - Filter the results by a specific category so that only its sub children are returned
        rootOnly - Determines whether to return only root categories
        sortField - The column to sort the search on. Possible values include: ID, CREATED, UPDATED, ACTIVE, NAME, DISPLAY
        descending - The order to return the search results
        start - The record to begin the return set on
        limit - The number of records to return
        activeOnly - Determines whether to return only active categories
        Returns:
        SearchResponse<CategoryResponse>, or a SirqulResponse with an error message
        Throws:
        SirqulException - the SirqulException. A custom exception type specifically thrown by this Sirqul SDK.
